Column Comment.0: INTEREST SET IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the interest set.
Column Comment.1: BA INTEREST SET SEQUENCE NUMBER: unique sequencing component to allowverioning of the interest set over time.
Column Comment.2: INTEREST SET IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the interest set.
Column Comment.3: BA INTEREST SET SEQUENCE NUMBER: unique sequencing component to allowverioning of the interest set over time.
Column Comment.4: INTEREST SET CROSS REFERENCE OBSERVATION NUMBER: Surrogatecomponent added to allow interest sets to relate to each other multiple ways.
Column Comment.5: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.6: CONTRACT ID: Unique identifier for the contract table.
Column Comment.7: EFFECTIVE DATE: the date on which this row of data first came into effect from abusiness perspective.
Column Comment.8: EXPIRY DATE: the date on which this row of data is no longer in effect from abusiness perspective.
Column Comment.9: BA INTEREST SET CROSS REFERENCE TYPE: The type of relationship betweeninterest sets. Interest sets may supercede each other, have an impact on the networth of the interest set etc.
Column Comment.10: BUSINESS ASSOCIATE: Unique identifier for a business associate, such as aperson, company, regulatory agency, government or consortium.
Column Comment.11: BUSINESS ASSOCIATE: Unique identifier for a business associate, such as aperson, company, regulatory agency, government or consortium.
Column Comment.12: PARTNER OBSERVATION NUMBER: This column is used when a businessassociate holds more than one interest share of a specific interest type (working,production etc) in a partnership. This can happen as a result of corporate mergers orasset acquisitions. If a partner only holds one interest share, this number will alwaysbe 1. Please note that this column should not be used to track multiple interest types;in this event, a new interest set must be created.
Column Comment.13: PARTNER OBSERVATION NUMBER: This column is used when a businessassociate holds more than one interest share of a specific interest type (working,production etc) in a partnership. This can happen as a result of corporate mergers orasset acquisitions. If a partner only holds one interest share, this number will alwaysbe 1. Please note that this column should not be used to track multiple interest types;in this event, a new interest set must be created.
Column Comment.14: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.15: PROVISION ID: unique identifier for a contract provision
Column Comment.16: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.17: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.18: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.19: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.20: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.21: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.22: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.23: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.24: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
